frameDefinitions: A Topical_entity has properties which are affected by the existence and association of an Entity.
An Item becomes filled with a Substance as a result of movement of liquid into visible or invisible interstices in the Item.
An Agent acts according to a <em>
In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. '' 'In her heart she must retain bitterness against those who had killed him.'
A Speaker communicates about a Topic in such a way as to mislead an Addressee, either by telling outright lies or by presenting a message in a misleading form.
A Cognizer applies oneself to commit a Pattern to memory, so that the Cognizer would recognize future examples of the Pattern or be able to reproduce it.
frameExamples: By the 1920s a characteristic book <t>had</t> black and white photographic illustrations only .
Paper and board <t>absorb</t> moisture in the winter.
Health authorities say they have put measures into <t>effect</t> in all ports of entry and in centers of provinces.
In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
I <t>lied</t> to you about your Christmas present.
A gaggle of students were frantically <t>memorizing</t> the answers out in the hall.
listRoleDefinitions: Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist and be associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
The entity under discussion, whose states and properties are impacted by its association with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> exists and is associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>
The place where the <fen>Entity</fen> is associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Item</fen> is the absorbant friendly thing that takes in the <fen>Substance</fen>.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the material that is taken in by the <fen>Item</fen>.
When the <fen>Item</fen> takes in <fen>Substance</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Item</fen> takes in <fen>Substance</fen>.
The <fen>Plan</fen> is a goal or purpose that the <fen>Agent</fen> carries out.

The <fen>Agent</fen>, often an institution or governmental organization, puts a <fen>Plan</fen> into effect. The Agent is generally a primary participant in the <fen>Plan</fen>, but a separate <fen>Focal_participant</fen> may be specified.
This role describes the medium through which a plan was executed.  It may occur in the same syntactic position as the Agent.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the Agent puts the <fen>Plan</fen> into effect.

The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Plan</fen> is or is not operational.

[CHANGE: or, place where agent puts into effect? 2 fes?]
The person who has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which the <fen>Agent</fen> possesses for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The person who uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey a deceptive Message to the Addressee.
The person that receives a Message from the Speaker.
<fen>Topic</fen> is the entity to which the proposition or propositions  relate, that they are about.
The time at which the deception occurs.
The location at which the deception occurs.
The sentient being that focuses on a <fen>Pattern</fen> so that it will remain in the memory.
The phenomenon that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> observes and commits to memory.
The time when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> memorizes the <fen>Pattern</fen>.
The location wherein the <fen>Cognizer</fen> memorizes the <fen>Pattern</fen>.
listRoleExamples: The policy will be implemented <fex>by a new computer system</fex>.
At all times <fex>the Saxon government</fex> held on to its insistently practiced political tradition.
Once you've got a War Bond, hang on to <fex>it</fex> for the full ten years of its life.
Margerite held on to the key <fex>on Wednesday</fex> until I returned to pick it up.
He will retain <fex>in his heart</fex> the memory of the vast Holocaust.
<fex>Politicians</fex> do nothing but tell lies about money.
You deceived me <fex>about the location of the diamonds</fex>.
<fex>I</fex> have memorized two kinds of knowledge from Allah's Apostle
Impress your friends by memorizing <fex>your phone numbers</fex> and throwing away your PDA!
Herbert Kornfeldt memorized his speech <fex>in the mailroom</fex>.
